title: Recovery
author: danielle
text: darkness,  it surrounds me and covers me like a blanket,  like there's no hope.  everyone crowds me and comforts me,  but it won't just wash away with soap.   despair,  i can feel it eating its way inside me,  i feel like i've been boxed and put away,  still waiting to be set free.   i've been told not to think of myself as a victim,  but it made me realise more.  that people suddenly woke up,  paying more attention to me than before.   hope,  it suddenly finds its way to my heart,  and now i wonder why it wasn't there from the very start.   gods hand is over me,  i know that know.  as i see the light coming at the end of the dark tunnel,  i ask god to take a bow.   no longer desperately trying to piece together broken glass,  i am even more determined than before to excel in everything and not just pass.   life is short,  make the best of it,  for you are destined to be more,  than trampled on piece of chewing gum stuck to the cold hard floor.    and remember to thank god for protecting you and all,  for without him you would stumble and fall.   recovered,  renewed,  refreshed,  and ready to start again.

title: The Friendship Game
author: danielle
text: friends are the greatest gifts around,  real friends aren't the ones you simply pull out the lost and found.  they stick to you like glue and don't let go,  through sun,  storm,  sleet and even snow.  it's not about whether they remember your birthday,  or if they're the coolest kids in school.  i'ts not about being the smartest,  or the quickest in the swimming pool.  so what if they're rich,  who cares if they're poor? the loyal,  kind,  supportive ones,  are the true friends for sure.  the brightest in the flower bed,  the top mark in the grade.  real friends are those who stand by you,  and would take a forceful grenade.  treasure them like gold,  treat them the same.  for if you are a true friend,  you'll win the friendship game.  and when you win and you are a phenomonal friend in every way,  a true friend you'll find and you will thank destiny you found her everyday.

title: Ode to my Bicycle
author: danny
text: you make getting to places much easier with a zoom.  you yell at me where to go,  but i just turn for you.   you wait every winter patiently for me to come to you.   your wheels are cool with that dark black.  youâ’ve saved me from many capturing cops in our game.  you make the wind blow in my face when we go down a hill.   you make stopping a lot easier with your breaks.  you can go over rocks while the others could not.  every time you run above a large lump i feel like i will come right off.   you can climb mountains while i cannot.  when we crash,  i hear a large thud.  you could not be any more perfect for me.  morning rides seem a lot more relaxing with you.  i always make sure to watch for cars when we cross the road when itâ’s time for me to put you away,  i only wish you could work in the snow.  life is a lot easier with you around,  but now only if you could survive in the winter.

title: Hidden Below
author: danyelle
text: even if you climb the highest tree,  there are things you still can't see,  and it will never again be fun for me.   where i am hidden i have not told,  but it is very cold.  in here everything is way too old.  there is not much mold.   i am hidden in a place just right,  but here's a clue: it isn't bright.  you would never be able to fly a kite,  even if you tried with all your might.   it hurts being down here,  all alone.  i lie here all day long; day and night i try to moan,  and i will never again hear a song.   i will never again see a bird fly,  or see its babies go bye bye.  i will never taste the cherry as i often did,  and i liked them a lot,  as a kid.   i will never again touch the softness of my bear,  but i will always care.  i will never touch the roughness of my couch,  and never again say 'ouch'.   i will never again think of things,  like big beautiful butterfly wings.  i can't think of that special time,  when i got my first dime.   i guess i'll just wait until they come,  but i am very out of date,  and very numb.   it is far away beyond the sea,  and in this place it is only me,  maybe some things were meant to be,  because no one will ever see me.

title: Last Week of School
author: david
text: the last week of school  is like standing still in a long line.  checking bags at the airport or waiting for ice cream.  school is not over yet,  but every look out the window;   every song played on the radio; each time a sweltering wave of heat  flows through the classroom.  the pupils are reminded  that they are,   but a week away.  from three months of sun soaked glory.  as the clock winds down,  they are days  till ice cream every day.  on the final day,  they are hours away  from going to bed late,   because the sun never sets.  they are second in line now the wait is about to be over.  joyous smiles bubble upon their faces,  and as the final bell rings the wait is finally over.

title: The Bike Ride
author: drew
text: it started in wisconsin,  on the elroy sparta trail.  we started out on our bikes,  with myself in the tail.   our destination was the tunnel,  that trains used to pass through.  along the way the trees supplied a peaceful serene view.   we made it to the tunnel,  with its large wooden gates.  they stood there looking menacing,  as though waiting for our fates.   we walked right through the tunnel,  turned around,  and came back.  we then mounted on our bikes,  and again got back on track.   we were riding back to the entrance,  when my dad came up on me.  i panicked and i crashed.  blood gushed from my knee.   a sock got wrapped around it,  to stop unwanted pain.    then to make matters worse,  the trail quickly filled with rain.   i hopped up on the tag-along,  and my dad pulled me behind.  my brother rode on my bike the whole entire time.   mud was flying everywhere.  it was getting in our eyes.  by the time we made it back,  we were covered far above our thighs.   we finally got to our car,  all tired,  cold and wet.  this would be one experience that we would never,  ever forget!

title: Life is Color
author: eleanor
text: as red as the lava building up,  like a wave of anger ready to explode out of you like a firework.   as orange as an untamed fire,  that was set loose into a world full of unsuspecting victims.   as yellow as the brightest star,  shining like there's no tomorrow to weaken its glow.   as green as the dew- dipped grass,  that blankets the ground in the early sunday morning with life.   as blue as the weeping river,  as it cries and flows gently leaving behind tear stained rocks.   as purple as a rare orchid,  as it thrives in nature with only hope to survive.   as pink as embarrassment,  as it raids your body from your head to your toes.   as brown as the torn boot of an exhausted traveler,  as he searches to find the meaning of life in this convoluted world.   as black as the darkest cave,  as you plunge into the unknown in hopes to find the jewel of promise.   as colorful as a rainbow,  as it stretches across the clear sky with confidence and telling you to never give up.

title: In the Basement
author: ellie
text: the sounds come from downstairs,  it sounds like a large thunk.  so up i get and climb out of my nice and cozy bunk.  my feet hit the carpet as i stumble out of bed,  i go down the stairs and almost land on my head.  i hear the sound again and it comes from the floor,  i walk a little ways to the basement door.  it creaks as it opens and i wince at the sound,   i hope it doesnâ’t wake my brother who will come running down.  i stare into the darkness,  shadows covering me from head to toe,   i hope nothing jumps out,  friend or foe.  as i start down the stairs i hear a loud snap,  and i run up to my bedroom,  a thumping behind my back.  i finally stop and turn around,   and there is my dog lying on the ground.

title: Stop Terrorrism
author: emily
text: mourning   when i look around and see all this rubble,   i think ''how could bin ladin's men create so much trouble?''   their country always had so much pain,   how do we know they would cause so much pain?   you can't say when you think of this you won't shed a tear,   because you and i both know there was somone who died there we loved and held dear.      weeping willow.    have you ever seen a weeping willow swaying in the breeze?,   it looks so sad and lonley compared to the other trees   kind of like us waiting for our families to burst out of the rubble,   then end all our mourning and trouble   so the next time you see weeping willow trees,   think of the buildings and deaths of the people swaying in the night breeze.    war.    it was 12:00 noon when bush announced war,   when our eagles took flight to soar,    we cry and rebuild our thoughts,   and on top of the rubble grows forget-me-nots,    the flowers unfortunately show,   america will never forget this pain and sorrow.

title: Signs of Courage ''9/11 heroes''
author: emily
text: they woke up that morning with a smile on their face,  with no idea what was about to take place.   talking,  laughing,  smiling with glee,  off goes the alarm,  it was trouble,  it had to be.   they raced and raced,  â‘till they got to the spot,   it was worse than they had thought.   listening to the screams,  as if an accident had occurred,  they knew it was an accident until they heard…  another plane?  what?  no way! â“it is too high!â” the heroes would say.   screaming,  shouting,  people jumping,  water coming out of the hose; they were pumping.   people were dying,  one after the other,  strangers and families hugging each other.   the heroes knew this was no mistake,  all of these lives bad people would take!  all those heroes that risked their lives,  for the people trapped in the building with strife.   while the heroes were in the south tower,  they all heard rumbling that had lots of power.   they picked up as many people as they could,  some got out,  but many never would.   the tower collapsed! oh! my! oh! no! everyone watching let their feelings show.   everyone rushing,  looking like ghosts,  from all of the ashes,  rubble,  and smoke.   the heroes ran in the north tower,  wishing that they had more power.   the heroes hurried in,  grabbed people and ran,  people not knowing that it was the taliban.   everyone hoping it was just a dream,  but it wasnâ’t,  it was as real as could seem.   the second tower had just gone down,  many people not to be found.   even though many people lost their lives,  america has stayed together with our hellos and goodbyes.   those heroes are fireman if you did not know,  let your appreciation come out and show.   we thank god for these people with all our hearts,  that america will not tear apart.   everyone remember that we are one…   one nation one community and one family- - for now and evermore.

title: Unknown
author: emily
text: a barren heart,  in a strange land.  taken from heaven,  by a gentle hand.   its passion is true,  its mind is pure,  its thoughts were so simple,  now not that sure.   cry to the window,  cry to the pain,  cry to yourself,  in a pit of shame.   take my hand,  before you leave.  take the time,  to understand me.  for time is lost,  and so are you.  immortal tears shall form a new,  a path in which,  i shall follow.  to a watery grave,  for all the morrows.   and two days past,  my beckoning call.  watch as i rise,  but watch as i fall.  for sorrow strikes,  with up most accuracy.  no longer you,  and no longer me.

title: Poems
author: emily
text: poems do not tell of when and where.  they are not here and there.  they tell a story,  one long forgot.  they say the things that we bare not.  the things long forgot.  they sing they dance,  they prance along the page.  for they will not fade.  they say words of inspiration,  only the perspiration,  of generations.  they do not tire,  some may gaze into a fire.  they do not pass by like wind,  they stay there; forever be,  in prosperity.  they do not wither,  nor they hither,  when thought upon they be.  instead they sing they shout,  they cry,  they weep,  for they are the things long forgot.

title: Sea Coast
author: emily
text: the gold whipped sun falls in midai,  and the amber leaves gently rustle.  soft shallow sand shakes the hand of the blue kissed sea.   sharp winds beat the grass,  as the waves dance.   soon the skies are full,  with twinkling fireflies.

title: Forest
author: emily
text: a bear is a caring mother.  the trees a home to owls.  the water gently flows,  as the fish swim through it.  the deer graze in the meadow,  a worry not bestowed in their heads,  about the future their meadow will be.  the plows will soon take over.  quick find shelter! already that is gone,  where will they live? no where,  their homes taken from them.  they are forced to die.  their homes were cemented over,  their families crushed.  by the fate of humanity.

title: Summer
author: emily
text: filled with light are summer nights,  thanks to fireflies.   blessed are we to have the sea,  to wash away our heat.   this will not last,  so have a blast.  for short coming winter will be here.   take it in while it lasts,  school will soon approach.   the willows will whisper and wail,  for us to come back.   but for now lets just smile,  and go have tea.   let's race the wind,  and then let it carry us away.   we'll soak up the summer sun,  while we have fun.  waiting for winter nights.

title: Always
author: emily
text: no matter how loud i've yelled,  no matter how much i've screamed,  you still listen to me.   no matter how mean the words i say,  you still love me.   no matter how far i've ran,  or where i've been,  you still stand beside me.   you love me for who i am.  the good and the bad person.  you love me forever and ever,  always.

title: A Willabe
author: emily
text: a willabe is not you're friend.  it is scary as a monster.  as mean as an angry lion.  as terrible as a wasp.  it likes to take your toys,   and it will not share! it packs a great surprise,  when it hides under your bed.  for in it,  willabes like to put,  a nasty rattle snake!  a willabe is not a horrible monster,  but as gentle as a caring butterfly.  it's as nice as a bunny,  as gentle as a deer.  and as sweet as honey.  it likes to play hide-and-go-seek,  and it will always share.  it'll make you breakfast,  and hug you at night.   so what really is a willabe?

title: Moonlight Dance
author: emily
text: the sun's colorful scarf fills the sky,  birds are the only shadow of day.   the skies' eyes are sparkling,  as they hug the sun goodbye.   the moon slowly changes outfits,  as it prepares to shine.

title: Tell Me Why
author: emily
text: tell me why the suns so bright,  why the planes go into flight.   why the night turns to light,  and why mills aren't on hills.   tell me again why the cars go so far,  why i can't bike and take a hike.   tell me about why i wake late,  and the bus i do not take.   tell me the things that seasons bring,  the reasons i can't fling the rock.   tell me why i'd rather ride a mule,  than go to school.

title: Never Forgot
author: emily
text: though you aren't here,  you're never forgot.   though you can't sing,  you're never forgot.   though you can't talk,  you're never forgot.   though the loss we've got,  you're never forgot.   through the tough times and happiness,  you're never forgot.   isn't wonderful our memories will not rot?  we cry we weep we feel sorrow,  still you're never forgot.   the times we've had will always be and like you,  they're not forgot.   songs we sang,  the bells that rang,  will never fade away.  because in this world you're not forgot.   do we still bear the faith we've shared? the hope? the joy? the pain? that i will not know,  but one thing i do,  you are not forgot.  though you die,  my face arise,  once more in heaven i shall join you.   we are separate,  but not for long.   we shall be together once more.  the time has yet to come,  so i will never forget,  only the question dare i ask.   do you still love me? whatever the answer may be,  i will never forget you.   the trees will die away,  all the lilies will wither.  will you still love me?  if the sky turned black and took my soul,  would you still love me?

title: Friendship
author: emily
text: friendship is a precious gift,  they'll give you a helping hand,  when you need a lift,   friendships are a rare jewel,  they are very hard to find,  and if you try really hard,  you'll get a best friend like mine,   friendships are a night light,  that take away the fear,  they help fight evil monsters,  and dry every tear,   friendships are an angel,  sent from high above,  to care for us and show us how to love,   friendships are a garden,  and with love and care they grow,  but you can't just hide your friendship,  show it to the world,  so they'll know,   that you have a best friend,  and thats no lie,  that they'll always love you,  no matter how hard you try,  i will be best friends till we both lay down and die.

title: Run
author: emily
text: run,  the wind,  your feet,     pound        pound            pounding,  against the soft soil,  your heart        beat           beat             beating,  the pain in your side,          thump             thump              thumping,  it all aches,  it hurts,   you want to lie down,  you want to quit,  but you keep going,  you keep fighting,  no matter what,  you love it,  so you'll never want to stop,  stop the feeling,  yes,  it hurts,  but i wouldn't change the pain,  for the world,  i'll keep on,     run      run        running,  and when the race is done,  i'll leave,  and get ready for the next one,  short distance won't do,  it has to be long,       mile        after mile,  i won't stop,  i won't quit,  i'll stay strong,  and race again.

title: MEMORIES
author: emily
text: i remember when i could run and play,  without a care in the world   i remember when the sun shone on my face,  as i devoured sweet water melon   i remember when my family would play and laugh and sing,  in front of the fire place,  on a winter's chilling night   and now it is all gone,  as i lay here alone,  waiting for death,  to erase my heartbeat and breath   i remember when i would hug my sister   i remember when my mother would tuck me in at night   i remember when my father would sling me on his back,  and run around like a pony   even though death is near,  i still see their dead looking faces when i told them good bye for the last time   i remember the emptiness that hollowed my heart,  when they took me away,  away from the life that i knew and loved   but my favorite memory is yet to come    the memory of reunion

title: Uniformed Laces
author: emily
text: the swirling design,  stamped across our walls.   the bricks in tatters,   what could be the cause?  thatâ’s when the men came,   scowls across their faces,   making me scared,   wearing their fancy uniformed laces.   i went to the camp,   the wind blew hard and damp,   blood soaked the ground,   and that day i found,   why the design was there.    my head was  shaved,   my dignity gone,   where was that distant memory of happiness and peace,    little pink cupcakes with frosting covering my face?  now all i can remember is the swirling design,   all i can do is wear a scowl across my face,   and wonder what it would be like if the world didnâ’t have the fancy uniformed lace.

title: Stars Dreams
author: erica
text: oh! that my young life were a lasting dream! my spirit not awakâ’ning till the beam of an eternity should bring the morrow: yes! thoâ’ that long dream were of hopeless sorrow,  â“twere better than the dull reality of waking life to her whose heart shall be,  and hath been ever,  on the chilly earth,  a chaos of deep passion from her birth!        but should it be â– that dream eternally continuing-as dreams have been to me in my young girlhood- should it thus be given,  â“twere folly still to hope for higher heaven! for i have revellâ’d,  when the sun was bright in the summer sky; in dreamy fields of light,  and left unheedingly my very heart in climes of mine imagining- apart from mine own home,  with beings that have been of mine own thought- what more could i have seen?   â“twas once and only once and the wild hour from my remembrance shall not pass â– some power or spell had bound me â– â‘twas the chilly wind came oâ’er me in the night and left behind its image on my spirit,  or the moon shone on my slumbers in her lofty noon too coldly â– or the stars â– howeâ’er it was that dream was as that night wind â– let it pass.         i have been happy â– thoâ’ but in a dream.  i have been happy â– and i love the theme â– dreams! in their vivid colouring of life â– as in that fleeting,  shadowy,  misty strife of semblance with reality which brings to the delirious eye more lovely things of paradise and love â– and all our own! than young hope in her sunniest hour hath known.

title: Star Haunted Palace
author: erica
text: in the greenest of our valleys by good angels tenanted,  once a fair and stately palace â– radiant palace â– reared its head.  in the monarch thoughtâ’s dominion â– it stood there!  never seraph spread a pinion over fabric half so fair!        banners yellow,  glorious,  golden,  on its roof did float and flow â– (this â– all this â– was in the olden time long ago)  and every gentle air that dallied,  in that sweet day,  along the ramparts plumed and pallid,  a winged odor went away.         wanderers in that happy valley,  through two luminous windows,  saw spirits moving musically,  to a luteâ’s well-tuned law,  round about a throne where,  sitting,  porphyrogene,  in state her glory well befitting the ruler of the realm was seen.         and all with pearl and ruby glowing was the fair palace door,  through which came flowing,  flowing,  flowing,  and sparkling evermore,  a troop of echoes whose sweet duty was but to sing.  in voices of surpassing beauty,  the wit and wisdom of their queen.         but evil things,  in robes of sorrow,  assailed the monarchâ’s high estate.  (ah,  let us mourn! â– for never morrow shall dawn upon her,  desolate!) and round about her home the glory that blushed and bloomed,  is but a dim-remembered story of the old-time entombed.         and travelers,  now,  within that valley,  through the encrimsoned windows see vast forms that move fantastically to a discordant melody,  while,  like a ghadtly rapid river,  through the pale door a hideous throng rush out forever and laugh â– but smile no more.

title: Star's Dream-Land
author: erica
text: by a route obscure and lonely,  haunted by ill angels only,  where an eidolon,  named night,  on a black throne reigns upright,  i have reached these lands but newly from an ultimate dim thule- from a wild weird clime that lieth,  sublime,  out of space- out of time.         bottomless vales and boundless floods,  and chasms,  and caves,  and titan woods,  with forms that no man can discover for the dews that drip all over; mountains toppling evermore into seas without a shore; seas that restlessly aspire,  surging,  unto skies of fire; lakes that endlessly outspread their lone waters â– lone and dead,  - their still waters â– still and chilly with the snows of the lolling lily.         by the lakes that thus outspread their lone waters,  lone and dead,  - their sad waters,  sad and chilly with the snows of the lolling lily,  - by the mountains â– near the river murmuring lowly,  murmuring ever,  - by the grey woods,  - by the swamp where the toad and the newt encamped,  - by the dismal turns and pools where dwell the ghouls,  - by each spot the most unholy â– in each nook most melancholy,  - there the traveler meets aghast sheeted memories of the past â– shrouded forms that start and sign as they pass the wanderer by â– white-robed forms of friends long given,  in agony,  to the earth â– and heaven.         for the hearts whose woes are legion â“tis a peaceful,  soothing region â– for the spirit that walks in shadow o! it is an eldorado! but the traveler,  travelling through it,  may not â– dare not openly view it,  never its mysteries are exposed to the weak human eye unclosed so wills its king,  who hath forbid the uplifting of the fringed lid; and thus the sad soul that here passes beholds it but through darkened glasses.         by a route obscure and lonely,  haunted by ill angels only,  where an eidolon,  named night,  on a black throne reigns upright,  i have wandered home but newly from this ultimate dim thule.

title: In The Ocean Deep Beneath
author: erin
text: in the ocean deep beneath past it's glassy rippling waves there is a hidden key that leads us to a path,  a path that magically sweeps us away and puts us in a spellbinding trance.  this path is the ocean,  our future,  and our past.  a place where everything lasts this is the place we all yearn to be,  a place that we have yet to see but it is only time till we find that path,  in the ocean deep beneath.

title: Immune
author: ethan
text: school.   a dangerous place.   sticks and stones are not present.   but words are.   and their gift of whiplash is all but too painful.   much more than sticks,  or stones.   insults in what seem like the trillions.   oblivious adults.   school is a battlefield.   crossfire of oral insults can truly injure anybody who gets in their way.   however,  immunity is an option.   ignoring is that immunity.   it is a bulletproof vest in the crossfire.   they can,  and will,  shoot at you until their ammunition of insults is emptied.   even then,  rocks will be thrown.   but in the end,  it is all futile.   maintaining dignity is the key.   it will provide you with  self-respect,  and a good attitude.   i keep dignity close,  in fear of losing it,  and with it my sanity.  but one day. . .   one day,  when i have a good job,  we will see who is laughing then. . .

title: Forever Alone

title: Bio Poem for Fatima Nazir
author: fatima
text: fatima; quiet,  helpful,  sensitive,  artistic.  dreams to paint a world of peace,  who brushes strokes of laughter and ease.  wants to cure the sick and poor,  who plans to do that with hard work and much more.  wants to ride on dragons and fly like fairies,  whose wings spread out in the colours of cherries.  whose sword is weak but pen is strong,   whose words say music so ever calm.    who yearns to see every life free,   only filled with love and liberty.  who will work hard until the end,   when she grows old with lousy fashion trends.  who wanders â‘whyâ’ for every question,   unless itâ’s rude and must not be mentioned.   who loves chocolate except the unsugared kind,  who loves to draw with every twist in her mind.  whose mission is to stop fearing insects,  blood & war,  if she were to make peace before it tore.  who plans to abolish ignorance and poverty,  who plans to gain knowledge as one of her priorities.   whose determination will forever inspire,  and whose thoughts of freedom will never retire.  whose final ambition is to create love and peace.

author: fiona
text: written in the country gardens  all who are locked in the cement walls may hear,  those out in the black clouds,  please lend your ear â–   open the gates to the country greens â–  where natural planes fly and the angels lie with blooms everywhere which never die embellishing the worldâ’s brightest sheens  tread your feet on the soft green hair â–  aspiring for garden jewels with envy saying â‘goodbyeâ’ to all the ennui to escape from terrible notes5 to the best lair  chant your songs of sorrows here â–  to wash away tears and drive away jeers to invite the rustle and chirps of cheers and youâ’ll find the mirrors of your life clear  lie in the shadow of the apple trees â–  engulfed by a bed of roses red forgotten by the vexations past dread dissolving your moments in the heavenly breeze  and youâ’ll find happiness never seen on your way with lots of fragrances to enrich the day                        -\tfiona sunny  black clouds1: polluted air natural planes2: birds green hair3: grass garden jewels4: flowers terrible notes5: noises mirrors of your life6: eyes moments7: breaths

title: Under the Sea of Tears
author: fiona
text: under the sea of tears  live little creatures that shiver and there above on land are iron pillars pillars â– so rigid that they do not even quiver  when the creatures go up to get some light as they were â– for a long time â– kept in the dark they are pushed down by sly whales and if not so,  they are food for the shark  they collect many uncut diamonds each day and treasure them in their chests they get black rubies and colorless jewels from the sandy coast,  where the sun sets  now,  where the sun rises â–  under the sea of tears are little ants living a hard â– but short,  miserable life and fearing death by the feet of giants  the little ants struggle for breath they somehow get on and survive the giants wade across the sea,  stamping the ants and do not care how these poor things thrive  the ants ask the giants to lift them up and dream an end to their die-hard strife but the giants turn a deaf ear to their request and a blind eye to their dreams of better life  the giants,  decorated with ornaments have nothing else of good to spare but shapeless emeralds of wrath and disgust â–  the ants keep them in their chest in despair  all these treasures of unpolished gems,  the cries of the little and their sorrowful years will never be opened nor be found,  unless â–  some really curious person dives into the sea of tears             - fiona

title: Dreams
author: franny
text: a dream is sailing through blank waters.  a white world made of nothingness.  fragments of your experiences swim through your mind like little fish.  your memory is a huge net that swoops through the water.  the wide ocean is built on your thoughts.  memories fly by like seagulls.  the rhythmic waves keep time to your musical memories.  but,  you orchestrate your own symphony of thoughts.  the tide changes and so do your dreams.  so,  you slowly sail back to consciousness.

text: iâ’ve closed my eyes,  and made a prayer,  and wished my dreams come true.    iâ’ve dreamt upon prince charming,  riding by in shining armor as a handsome,  strong young knight.    iâ’ve wished of being a princess living in a royal castle with maids,  servants,  and slaves to hurry at my feet with one loud call.    iâ’ve longed for meeting santa claus,  fairies,  pixies,  and unicorns.    iâ’ve hoped to become a famous writer,  whoâ’s partner is the pen,  living large and famous with gold,  money and jewels to spare.    but as i grew,  iâ’ve learnt about reality,  and how sometimes things donâ’t come true.    how prince charming may not always arrive in shining armor,  how being a princes does not mean living in a castle,  how santa claus does not always become a real famous heroine,  how becoming a writer is not as easy as it sounds.    how learning of reality,  and the things going on here and there do not always make one happy.    but i hope that one day,  i can look at the sky see a shining twinkle gleam at a mindâ’s eye…  and wish upon a star once again.

title: What if...      Then...
author: gus
text: what if i couldn't walk? then i couldn't get around quicker.   what if i couldn't talk? then i'd have to learn sign language.   what if i couldn't eat? then i'd die in a matter of time.   what if i could not sleep? then i'd read every night.   what if i was tall? then i could slam dunk a basketball.   what if i was small? then i could not reach high places.   what if the world ended? then i'd go with it.   what if i survived and no one else did? then i'd survive until i couldn't live anymore.   what if i was poor and didn't have a family? then i'd get a job and build a family of my own.   is it worth living? maybe?!

title: ''A School Day''
author: hayley
text: getting up for school is such a struggle,  it's even worse than trying to juggle.  eating breakfast,  brushing your teeth,  doing you hair,  which is a battle that can sometimes be beat.  trying to catch the bus is such a rush,  then you get to school and all the teachers say hush.  religion,  science,  english,  history,  and reading too,  it is all so much i don't know what to do! then we break for lunch,  so we have a little time to munch,  and then it is time to go back to spanish,  special,  and math.  most kids can't wait to hear the bell,  so they can go home and get on their dell,  to talk to all of their friends on aol,  my bookbag is so big,  i hear the bell,  so i start to leave,  but i tripped and fell.  i make it to the bus,  but then i think of how school days can be such a fuss!

title: Seasons
author: haylw
text: seasons  winter snow glistens on the ground.  small,  gentle,  snowflakes fall onto everyone and everything.  children come to play almost every night and day.  next comes spring.   muddy puddles,  dirty shoes,  and the smell of dry leaves  and hardened mud.  next comes summerâ’s sizzling  sun.  humid air leaves you gasping,  waiting for rain to come so that you can finally breathe fresh,  cool air.   finally comes fall.   leaves dry up and crumble on the ground,  leaving a cold damp smell in the air.   the cool damp air is perfect for playing soccer.   lastly,  winter swoops back in,  making you wish for one more glimpse of summer.

title: Flutters Of Imagination
author: heather
text: maybe a little snore,  or wind brushing against the external decor.  a beam of translucent glow and crystals down below,  a gray glorious gem overhead with natural bowls that have been ''shade fed''.   pathway of hidden haze leads to the tree of firey blaze in the melancholy wood some people say if you should,  go into the plantation the luck will find imagination,  a gift that is to be used with finesse for it can grant eternal happiness.   up in the leaves you may find flutters that dash and disappear.  spurts of twinkle in the green below.  only the luck of the draw will know.   and when day comes the children will play.  but some will begin to build,  the housing in the roots of the tree.  for all fairies welcome and be thankful for the youths that add a moss bed and a pebble pillow too.  for it could be yours one of them visits tonight.   when you wake in thy morn,  don't forget to check the house you built for the pebble pillow to be misplaced,  or a small sparkle on the floor.  you never know,  they could have spent the night.

title: What if...   Then...
author: heather
text: ''what if?'' by: heather munsey     what if kids ruled the world? then the world would be sort of unorganized.     what if animals could talk? then we would be able to understand them.     what if kids told their parents what to do? then they would never be in trouble.     what if you could pause time? then life would be pretty neat.     what if you could chose your grade on your report card? then all kids would probably have all aâ’s on our report cards.      what if you could pick money off trees everyday? then we would all be rich.     what if you could eat anything and not get fat? then we all would be skinny.     what if you could drive at any age? then kids would be getting speeding tickets all the time.     what if you could meet famous stars whenever you want? then we would all be in heaven.     what if your room would clean itself? then parents would never think a tornado lived in your room.     what if your homework would get done by itself? then kids would be in heaven.     what if you could cheat on a test without getting caught? then you could pass all your tests all the time.     what if kids taught the teachers? then teachers will be the ones getting yelled at.     what if you had a genie and you had 1, 000 wishes a day? then the whole world would be in heaven.       what if you did not have to do chores? then i love my life.
